<HEADLINE>
White House opposes China anti-secession law
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
WASHINGTON, March 14
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The White House on Monday branded 
"unfortuante" China's adoption of a law giving its military the 
legal basis to attack Taiwan if the island moves towards 
independence.
</P>
<P>
"We view the adoption of the anti-secession law as unfortunate. 
It does not serve the purpose of peace and stability in the Taiwan 
Strait," spokesman Scott McClellan told reporters.
</P>
